    public class DepthEntryIncrementalDecorator
extends DepthDecoratorBase
implements IDepthEntryUpdateMessage
    Implements IDepthEntryUpdateMessage around a FIX market data incremental refresh message.

    Handles populating the static fields in the message and also updating the dynamic fields required in response to IDepthEntryUpdateMessage methods calls.

    Author:
    John Cameron

        Updates the standard fields associated with a depth entry update.
        Specified by:
        setStandardValues in interface IDepthEntryUpdateMessage
        Parameters:
        entryID - Entry ID value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryID field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryID)
        price - Price value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryPx field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryPx)
        qty - Quantity value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntrySize field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntrySize)
        side - Side associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryType field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryType). Indicates buy, sell or not specified. 0 - Not specified, 1 - Buy, 2 - Sell.

      • setValue

        public void setValue(IFixFieldInfo fixFieldInfo,
                     IMarketDataValue value)
        Description copied from interface: ISetValueStore
        Set the value on the message corresponding to the FIX field defined in the given fixFieldInfo.

        Note that fixFieldInfo includes, among other things, the FIX tag value and possible MDEntryType associated with this field.

        Only variable values of the reusable message should be set using this method. Any value set by this method is automatically assumed to be variable (ie cannot be reused).

        If mdEntryType is '\0', then the value is not part of an MDEntry - but is the field with the given FIX tag, outside the MDEntries part of the message.

        Specified by:
        setValue in interface ISetValueStore
        Parameters:
        fixFieldInfo - Defines the FIX field associated with the given value.
        value - Value for this field.
